body:
+1;
1. In general, function signatures can have the same line-width as other lines in the source-file. 
2. When introducing line breaks, don't break a param definition half-way

@bharathkk 
re: 1, good point about partition count monitor, let me see if / how we can fix that.
re: 2, I thought we moved side inputs out of the run loop to the CSM. Is the chooser bootstrap / priority configuration still relevant? I'd imagine the bootstrap for side inputs is handled by the CSM now, does it not look at the bootstrap configuration itself?

@bharathkk to take a look and see if this will be addressed in the metadata store work. Batching large number of writes will be an issue with any implementation, so perhaps this should be addressed at the API layer, either by supporting batch puts, or by accepting the JobModel (and other large messages like configs) as a whole and chunking internally within an implementation. Also, when we have versioning in metadata store, we should also not need to store the job model in ZK.

@shanthoosh I don't like that we'e diverging in both the code path and key name for job models in ZK and YARN. The end state when metadata store is available should be a consistent code path to read and write job models from anywhere, including Samza dashboard. IMHO it'll be better to do this inside the ZKMetadataStore implementation since this is a temporary fix. WDYT?

@shanthoosh Also, do you need to store and read with a checksum for the multi-part read?

> (2) When the container that we saved in step1 dies, the AM on receiving this callback does nothing about it.

@xinyuiscool: 
what's the root-cause for (2)? the expected behavior to request resources for it from the ClusterManager and restart it

@sborya 
1. I've moved the chunking logic into the zookeeper metadata store implementation.
2. I've already replied to checksum comment. I will add check-sum support in a immediate follow-up patch. Also, this check-sum for identifying data corruption is not required for `JobModel` alone in standalone. It is applicable to all kind of metadata stored in YARN and standalone.

@prateekm 
Added checksum to the end of metadata-value in  `ZkMetadataStore`. It is used for verification during  read and published to zookeeper during write. 

Updated the PR with all the changes.

@atoomula 

I agree.
IMO command handers should NOT be environment variables. They are EXTENSIONs. They shall NOT be loaded by SET command. I prefer a load command instead.
